OL,6,F- Substandard post-procedure
OL,7,Fmanagement of a patient who should
OL,8,Fhave remained recumbent for at least
OL,9,Fone or two hours but was given no
OL,10,Finformation about follow-up care.
OL,12,FIn his assessment of how the blood
OL,13,Fpatch procedure was performed, the
OL,14,Fjudge said there seemed little dispute
OL,15,Fthat the plaintiff received an
OL,16,F"appalling standard of care".
OL,18,FHe went on to find that she had
OL,19,Festablished liability against both
OL,20,Fdefendants on a joint basis.
