OL,6,F"It could be said that the root cause
OL,7,Fof the plaintiff's injuries was the
OL,8,Fnegligent misdiagnosis of the first
OL,9,Fdefendant acting in his private
OL,10,Fcapacity," Mr Justice Colton
OL,11,Facknowledged.
OL,13,F"That said, there clearly was a
OL,14,Ffailure on behalf of (the Trust) to
OL,15,Fensure proper governance, including a
OL,16,Flack of review and failure to obtain
OL,17,Finformed consent, in respect of the
OL,18,Ffirst defendant's actions."
